items.name: 【Art Style】Stanley Lau (Artgerm) Style
items.description:
2023/7/27 update

Add some comic covers to the dataset. Process the edges of the sketches to remove pixels that are irrelevant to the training content. Retrain the model using new craft.

Introduction

A LoRA model trained with images illustrated by Stanley Lau (Artgerm). No trigger tag. 0.6 ~ 0.8 weights are good. The preview images are generated using 1.6 version, 2.0 version Yesmix and MeinaMix to verify the compatibility of this LoRA model on different base models. By the way, you can input marker \(medium\) to generate sketches of characters.

Cautions (Must Read)

For anime model,

pls disable 'face restoration' during generating.

pls disable 'face restoration' during generating.

pls disable 'face restoration' during generating.

  • Some preview images are generated using 'Hires Fix' and upscaled using 'SD Upscale'. Thus, if you wanna generate the preview images, pls download the original preview images and analyze them using 'PNG INFO' in webui to get all generating information.

BTW, make sure set this option in 'Stable Diffusion' settings to 'CPU' to successfully regenerate the preview images with the same seed.

  • The training resolution of this model is 1024x1024, so generating resolution must not exceed this range. Try to use 'hires fix' to prevent this problem and help to generate higher-resolution images.

  • For 784mb VAEs (NovelAI, Anythingv3, Orangemix, Counterfeit) users, make sure add '--no-half-vae' in command line of webui to prevent generating black images. See voldy's log for the details of edit method. For high-performance GPU, make sure 'medvram' and 'lowvram' mode are disabled.

items.name: Lilly & Luna (Synthetic)

This is Lilly & Luna. Trained by working with over 400 fictional Stable Diffusion outputs to get the style and looks that we wanted. Lilly & Luna were trained in the nude so NSFW themes are to be expected as this is what we wanted when creating her for Nudes.AI.

We're happy with the style and output from Lilly & Luna and have created a persona and chat which you can interact with over on our site. We also wanted to make it so anyone can use these females on their own computers.

Generally using 2girl term in the prompt along with the textual inversion trigger leads to better results. This was really an experiment to see if we could train 2 characters into a single textual inversion.

License terms as follows;

  • No online generation services without written permission.

  • No renaming the character if publishing output images online.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

Building a good prompt with my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (c4rmr0se:0.99), a woman as a movie star, modelshoot style, (extremely detailed CG unity 8k wallpaper), photo of the most beautiful artwork in the world, professional majestic oil painting by Ed Blinkey, Atey Ghailan, Studio Ghibli, by Jeremy Mann, Greg Manchess, Antonio Moro, trending on ArtStation, trending on CGSociety, Intricate, High Detail, Sharp focus, dramatic, photorealistic painting art by midjourney and greg rutkowski, (white turtleneck top:1.2), ((movie premiere)), (long skirt), ((standing near a movie theater)), ((paparazzi in the background)), (looking at viewer:1.2), (detailed pupils:1.3), ((closeup portrait:1.1))"

Esteemed and enigmatic recipient,
The quivering quill of this distrustful pirate ventures to capture the final words and musings of a soul betrayed by life and, in turn, relentless in its betrayals. In this missive, which trembles to the rhythm of the waves and dissipates in the saline wind, I wish to share with you the tale of my last legacy and treasure.
In my wanderings through the unfathomable depths of the sea, I have learned that trust is a luxury we mortals should not pride ourselves on. Throughout my days, I have witnessed how the sweetest promises and loyal alliances dissolve like the nectar of twilight. Therefore, I firmly embrace my skeptical nature, scrutinizing each word and deed for hidden treachery.
Change, that inexorable compass governing existence itself, has taught me that certainties are ephemeral. Winds shift direction without warning, ocean currents divert our course, and tides carry our destinies away. Hence, amid the uncertainty that dances upon the surface of the seas, I have decided to construct and safeguard this treasure. A legacy that will endure beyond my wanderings, an eternal and immutable offering.
Thus, I lay before your eyes this treasure, concealed within the embrace of these words, so that on the inevitable day when adventures fade and the seas languish, you may unveil it and claim it as your own. No matter what may transpire, be it adverse winds that blow or storms that assail your path, this fortune shall endure as a beacon in the darkness, a jewel of unalterable worth.
Within this chest of words and enigmas, you shall find the keys to unravel the deepest secrets of the seas. Maps sketched with the skill of a wandering cartographer will guide you to unexplored lands and buried treasures. You will discover songs whispered by sirens, intoxicating your senses and compelling you to dance in eternity. You will contemplate the words that recount the tales of forgotten pirates and anonymous heroes, whose exploits shall resound in the sea breeze.
And thus, as time passes and the currents exert their influence, when the final grain of sand has fallen in the hourglass of the seas and the waves cease to whisper their secrets, this legacy shall rise as a silent witness of a golden past. Then, oh intrepid seeker, you shall be the custodian of the history that pulses through the veins of the ocean, the guardian of words that have survived oblivion.
May this letter, emissary of a weary and weathered pirate, find its recipient in you, one who comprehends the truth concealed within my distrust and the reason behind this missive. You, who still carry the flame of adventure in your heart and the bravery of the seas in your eyes, have been chosen to receive this treasure, offered as a final farewell and most precious inheritance.
With fervent hope and a heart in the abyss, Tomas Agilar

items.name: Realia Photorealistic
items.description:
Realia is a photorealistic model. It is a flexible model without rigid requirements. The prompt you get from anywhere will work fine. It will give consistent results at low resolution or high resolution. There are elements of creativity in it, so you can produce fantasy-style things without having to stick to strict realism.

Usage:

-Eular a, DPM++2s Kerras, DPM++SDE Keras and DPM++2M SDE Keras.

-Eular a gives good results even with 25 steps, but the more effort the better. With one of the DPMs you will see amazing results with 30-40 steps.

-512x512, 512x768 gives not bad results, but the resolutions it is good at are higher resolutions like 768x768, 768x1024.

-It works best with detailed prompts, but with simpler prompts it is okay to leave the result to the model.

Shortcomings, problems:

-When you try to produce an fantasy style image, some textures may be CG. This is related to how far it is from reality.

-Some portrait photos may produce two faces with a low probability. Try a second time or change the seed and it will be fixed.

This is a model that I've been working on for a long time and wanted to release when it was perfected, but it took longer and longer to develop. With the release of the XL version, I decided to release it.

This model, which consists of many trainings and hundreds of merges, really took a lot of work. I hope you will like it.

"We all have secrets, of one kind or another." -Vivienne

Anna Henrietta who ? -soul3142


This work is licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-NoDerivatives 4.0 International License.

If you want to, you can support me on Patreon or Buy me Coffee.

My Witcher LoRA Index - soul3142's Guide to the Witcher Universe. additionally you can check out some characters i've made from other games also.

Main Trigger Word - vivienneW3_soul3142 , check examples for other ones.

RECOMMENDATIONS :-

  1. Highres Fix - must, if you are getting blurry and ugly images

    My upscale method: txt2img 512x768 -> send to img2img -> controlnet tile upscale, tile diffusion 2x scale with 4xUltrasharp upscaler and tiled vae

  2. Weight: 0.6 - 0.8

  3. Clip Skip: 2

  4. Denoising - Don't go too high, it can alter a lot of details

  5. For better face's - you can use ADetailer

I use 0.7 weight, 25 steps, Euler a, Clip skip 2 in nearly all my examples with almost same, simple +ve/-ve prompts regardless of checkpoint for my own consistency purposes.

There are imperfections here & there, which i usually leave it in as is, (i never do any inpainting in examples), most of which like hands can be fixed with better prompting, negative embeddings while other like weapons are just bad majority of the time no matter the model as of today.

Some LoRA's are flexible with any clothing, some are not (usually character's with single costume) so keep these things in mind.

This is an unofficial fanmade LoRA, not intended for any commercial purpose and use. All characters and IP rights are owned by their respective creators and owners. I do not own rights to any of these characters.

items.name: King (One punch man)
items.description:
Model used: AbyssOrangeMix3

Recommended VAE: orangemix or kl-f8

Recommended LoRA weight: 0.8-1

Trigger words: king, anime, one punch

Recommended words in prompt: 1boy, blonde hair, solo, scar, blue eyes, long hair

Negative prompt example:

(worst quality, low quality:1.4), 3d, greyscale, monochrome, text

On all images from preview I used DPM++ 2M SDE sampler, but you can use what you like.

All other settings the same as for AOM model:

Steps:

  • DPM++ SDE Karras: Test: 12～ ,illustration: 20～

  • DPM++ 2M Karras: Test: 20～ ,illustration: 28～

Clipskip: 1 or 2

Upscaler :

  • Detailed illust → Latenet (nearest-exact)
    Denoise strength: 0.5 (0.5~0.6)

  • Simple upscale: Swin IR, ESRGAN, Remacri etc…
    Denoise strength: Can be set low. (0.35~0.6)

This LoRA was trained on images which I scraped from fancaps.net (I made tampermonkey extension which adds a download button under each image). I used wd14 tagger extension for Stable diffusion to automatically tag my images and LoRA trainer colab for training (42 images with 6 repeats, 2 batch size, 10 epochs).

I plan to do a lot of LoRAs based on the One Punch Man anime. If you are interested, you can follow me.

-Steps: 30-50

__________________________________________________________________________________

Workflow for my images -

  • Please use the BerryMix VAE ensure your image has correct color

  • Use Adetailer (After Detailer) extension to improve many things such as faces, bodies and hands. Other Adetailer models can also be found on Civitai and Huggingface:

  • Hires fix with denoising strength of 0.3 - 0.35, using upscaler "x_NMKD-Superscale-SP_178000_G":

  • Move the hires image to img2img, using a denoising strength of 0.3-0.35 and keeping the same prompt, negative prompt, settings (cfg, CLIP, steps, sampling), AND seed. Generate this image, (MAKE SURE TO USE THE NEW HEIGHT GIVEN AFTER HIRES), this will inject more color and detail into your image:

  • Next move this new Img2img generation back into Img2img once again keeping the same prompts, settings and seed, but with a LOW denoising strength 0.1-3.0 (sometimes at high denoising strength 2.0-3.5 it will create eyes and faces inside of your image). Use the SD upscale script with the "RealESRGAN_x4plus_anime_6B" sampler to increase your image size:

(Civitai lowered the quality so you cant't tell, image on left is 512x768, image on right is 4096 x 6144, 8x THE SIZE!)

items.name: SDXLMixSampler - ComfyUI JNode (Workflow Included)
items.description:
To support my work, you could buy me a coffee

https://www.buymeacoffee.com/JasonAICreator

SDXLMixSampler 1.1

The node updated to accept loop:number rather total_steps:number

The total_steps would be calculated as mix_steps*loop

add final_only input to determine output multiple images or only the final loop image

If fina_only set to no, it would produce each loop image in output

SDXLMixSampler

The concept is to make one node to use both base+refiner like simple sampler.

Let me explains some parameter.

total_steps: total steps would run with this sampler. default is 20.

mixing_steps: total steps of one loop, loop = total_steps / mixing steps

base_steps_percentage: the percentage of base model's steps in each loop, the refiner would take the leftover

The whole pocess would only add_noise at the first base model sampling, other would disable_noise. The return_with_leftover_noise would be false at the last refiner node.

Why would I create this node? I was testing around generating text and I found it helps to generating text in multiple loop of the base+refiner process and I think it could done by 1 node.

All my custom_nodes would goto the flowing git page:

https://github.com/lrzjason/ComfyUIJasonNode/tree/main

Contact:

欢迎加群讨论AI相关的话题，遇到问题有能力的我会尽量解答

验证：小志Jason

items.name: Eddie Murphy Lora
items.description:
Hehehehehe

Be nice, have fun!

Edward Regan Murphy (born April 3, 1961)[2] is an American actor and comedian. He rose to fame on the sketch comedy show Saturday Night Live, for which he was a regular cast member from 1980 to 1984. Murphy has also worked as a stand-up comedian and is ranked No. 10 on Comedy Central's list of the 100 Greatest Stand-ups of All Time.[3] Murphy has received a Grammy Award and an Emmy Award and was honored with the Mark Twain Prize for American Humor in 2015 and the Golden Globe Cecil B. DeMille Award in 2023.[4][5]

Murphy has received Golden Globe Award nominations for his performances in 48 Hrs. (1982), the Beverly Hills Cop series (1984–present), Trading Places (1983), The Nutty Professor (1996), and Dolemite Is My Name (2019). He has also won numerous awards for his work on the fantasy comedy film Dr. Dolittle (1998) and its 2001 sequel. In 2007, Murphy won the Golden Globe for Best Supporting Actor and received a nomination for the Academy Award for Best Supporting Actor for his portrayal of soul singer James "Thunder" Early in the musical film Dreamgirls.[6]

Murphy has worked as a voice actor, including roles playing Mushu in Disney's Mulan (1998), Thurgood Stubbs in the sitcom The PJs (1999–2001), and Donkey in the Shrek franchise (2001–2010), the latter of which he earned a BAFTA Award for Best Actor in a Supporting Role nomination. In some films he plays multiple roles; this is intended as a tribute to one of his idols, Peter Sellers. He has played multiple roles in Coming to America (1988), Vampire in Brooklyn (1995), the Nutty Professor films, Bowfinger (1999), The Adventures of Pluto Nash (2002), Norbit (2007), and Meet Dave (2008). His recent films include Tower Heist (2011), Dolemite Is My Name (2019), Coming 2 America (2021), and You People (2023).

In 2020, he won his first Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Guest Actor in a Comedy Series for hosting Saturday Night Live.[7] Murphy's films have grossed over $3.8 billion ($6.5 billion adjusted for inflation) in the United States and Canada box office,[8] and over $6.7 billion worldwide.[9] In 2015, his films made him the sixth-highest grossing actor in the United States.[10][8] As a singer, Murphy has released three studio albums, including How Could It Be (1985), So Happy (1989), and Love's Alright (1993). He is also known for singing the hit song "Party All the Time" in 1985.

items.name: Bipedal Tactical Mecha
items.description: Most of the bipedal mecha LoRAs here were of the fantasy genre, appearing excessively pristine for warfare weaponry. Therefore, I trained a LoRA model based on majicMIX realistic v6, hoping to make the generated mechas more rugged. I used weight 1.0 for this LoRA.

items.name: [Tsumasaky] Remitsu Mix
items.description:
✨✨Want your personalized LoRA or illustrations?✨✨

Commissions on Buymeacoffee or Ko-fi

🐦 Twitter | 🎨 Pixiv | 📷 Instagram

About

Some of you asked me to share my personal model. After some refinements and consistency tests, it finally here. This is huge merge that contains some checkpoints that I like:

  • Ivory

  • Toonify

  • NAI

  • Anything 3

  • AlphaLyrai

All images samples were created with YOZORA.vae

This merge is capable of both male and female generations, but tends to work better with female characters. I tested this merge with a lot of character and style LoRAs, and the consistency is great, so don't mind burnt images, it never happened to me.

This is a no baked VAE version. So it works with most of them... But i recommend use VAEs that saturate images, i think it looks nicer and better.

For future versions, I'll try to bring a more cartoon look, but without throwing the 2.5d anime character that i like into the trash. It will be difficult, but we will try.

Feel free to use, enjoy or critisize.
